=m><span class=title>   Re: What do you think a wizard is the master of?</span><hr size=1> Heh I'm a big believer in buffing up wizzies, so couldn't resist doing this <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
&gt;Quotes on Psychodelia:<br>
&gt;Wizards are the best class vs. mobs that heal. A well<br>
&gt;placed stun or a large DD will prevent many things(such as<br>
&gt;myconid priests or dragons) from healing themselves.<br>
<br>
Other class can stun too so I wouldn't say wizards are the best at that. In fact when I try to stun, some enchanter usually beat me to it. Not sure if a large DD interupts casting, then again I never try to interupt casting with a DD<br>
<br>
&gt;Wizard direct damage indirectly heals the group. Instant<br>
&gt;massive damage eliminates the nead to melee it for that<br>
&gt;extra time, thus saving hit points and saving healer mana. <br>
<br>
You have sunstrike and such but I mainly attack with draughts; and 650ish damage doesn't save that much time IMO. It probly saves 10 sec probly and a warrior doesn't lose much hit points in 10 sec against a single mob.<br>
<br>
&gt;Wizards can attack from long range and their damage is<br>
&gt;automatic. This is essential on large raids, when melee<br>
&gt;classes can often loose sight of the mob, get in each<br>
&gt;others way, or suffer from a close range NPC attack(such<br>
&gt;as area effect)<br>
<br>
It is dangerous for casters to cast when the tanks lose sight of the mob. Without tanks taunting, the mob starts to take out the caster one by one. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upsychodelia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Psychodelia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 142<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/9/01 1:53:46 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/DIAN4/ec1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What do you think a wizard is the master of?</span><hr size=1> Im glad you addressed this Tuvack. Ill try and respond back if I may.<br>
<br>
What I meant by large DD stopping healing is that a high damage DD will kill the mob before it heals, not interrupt its casting. Other classes should use their stuns while the wizards use their DD on a healing mob. Landing a stun between the dd is a good strategy also when the mob is a healer.<br>
<br>
Concerning brainbite : Id rather talk about this in game. In short, I worship the use of this spell.<br>
<br>
<br>
Draughts are fine too. Also, wizards(if they use concussion effectively) dont take damage, they give it. And if they get hit, a skin spell should give them enough time to land a brainbite to taunt the mob off of them. Some stuff, like in the new Velious zones will summon and kill you unless you cast concussion between each nuke.<br>
<br>
More is lost in 10 seconds than just tank hit points. You can lose a spawn altogether. You can lose a cleric, lose an enchanter. You can lose the thing you are fighting. There are a million reasons why it is better to kill something fast. The best combo for killing something is about 50/50. A taunter for every wizard, not all melee. The reason is simple: Kill the creature/creatures before they kill you. This is why these new Velious gods with a million HPs are so hard now. They cant be killed quickly. Its as simple as that. (wizards certainly aren't masters against velkator(sp?)<br>
<br>
About tanks loosing sight of the mob, getting in the way etc:   <br>
True, it isn't safe to nuke when there isn't a taunter. But its much safer with concussion.  Direct damage has advantage over melee in that it has vast range. Think about this..Only so many tanks can simultaneously hit one mob at once, yet you could fill the entire lair with wizards who are constantly casting instant damage. Chances are the thing will be dead before it has any opportunity to do any serious harm. This is of course the raid scenario. The single group scenario most likely consists of several lower hp mobs. A wizard can blast down the first couple and let the rest of the group finish the lonely couple left while he meditates. Group says &quot;wow, we rock.&quot;<br>
<br>
Once again , I cant stress this enough:<br>
<br>
IF YOU ARE A WIZARD THAT PLANS ON DOING RAIDS IN VELIOUS&lt; YOU ARE GOING TO NEED BRAINBITE(CONCUSSION)<br>
cast it after every nuke you land on these high hit point mobs.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
