<br>
About large DD stopping healing, where do we find a fast and large enough DD? Good timing can eliminate the need of fast cast, but I think I've seen a mob starting to gate with 20% or more hp and I don't think any single pre-60 DD can kill it.<br>
<br>
I'll talk to you about brainbite in game if/when I activate my account again. I try not to let EQ take over my life <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . I have brainbite and I can relate to what you mean. Root used to be sufficient to safe own butts but brainbite is what keeps us alive against summoning mobs.<br>
<br>
&quot;More is lost in 10 seconds than just tank hit points. You can lose a spawn altogether. You can lose a cleric, lose an enchanter. You can lose the thing you are fighting.&quot;<br>
-spawns begin to cluster? use enchanters<br>
-lose groupmembers? they should learn to deal with aggro. We don't have the mana to burn down every mob they aggro if they do so too often anyway.<br>
-lose the mob due to gating/healing? everyone who can stun, should.<br>
<br>
Assuming a wizard can make a mob die 10 sec earlier with 1 nuke and benefit the group in all the various ways you described, a group doesn't always have a wizard and a good one at that, and thus will mostly likely not do things that require this special ability of wizzies... eg. a group will not say &quot;ok we have a wizzie. let's pull a few more mobs every cycle than before.&quot; (opposite of losing spawns) Conversely, do people specifically ask to group with a wizard so they can do more spawns? I think it might actually be the opposite because a mage do more total damage in one night. Also mages and druids are good wizard substitutes that can probly do 75% of the dmg of wizards in DD. This follows that you have to argue the 33% DD bonus over druid/mages is significant. IE a wizard makes a mob die 2 second faster by nuking than when replaced by a mage (excluding pet). Sorry to burst your bubble but wizard's single-target DD is not THAT wonderful:P especially when there is the mage class. We are good at AoE and not much more.<br>
<br>
In recap, a wiz is only superior as a damage dealer to a mage/druid by having brainbite and the +33% nuking bonus.<br>
But mage pets makes up the damage and druids are the 2nd best healer with the new added spell (nature's touch? not sure.)<br>
<br>
Anyway I'm glad I'm not a necro lol. 6 months ago I would have exchanged my wiz for a necro if possible after seeing a necro soloing frenzied ghoul room. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rayster>Rayster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 99<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/12/01 2:13:53 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What do you think a wizard is the master of?</span><hr size=1> I can't resist not replying, but wizard class in general is NOT the most efficient damage dealer in most experience group / long fight situation.  There really isn't much benefits when you kill a most fast because you will go out or low on mana on the next 5 or so mezzed mobs and rather become obsolete in the group when you have to med for the next 5 ro 8 minutes. Necromancer and magician can out damage a wizard any time in any long fight / exp group. The only time wizard is best / preferred class is when doing raid / dragon encounter (need lure spells / fast killing). This is what I feel. /shrug<br>
