Psychodelia and I went into the little details but Rayster painted the big picture quite accurately.<br>
<br>
All the tricks (eg. kill the first few mobs quickly in a pull) and benefits (eg. save time) of our DD's do not only apply to wizards, but many other caster classes too. Wizards are just slightly better at those after considering the slighly better efficiency and fast casting.<br>
<br>
(In fact, in the aspect of saving time by burning down mobs, wizards are only better because we are more flexible in that we can choose when to kill fast. Pet classes outdamage us in a long term if the pet's damage is included, thus save MORE time than wizards) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utuvack.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tuvack</A> at: 3/15/01 5:31:38 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upsychodelia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Psychodelia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 149<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/21/01 4:29:34 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/DIAN4/ec1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What do you think a wizard is the master of?</span><hr size=1> Where in my posts did I say that wizards were the best damage dealers in a long group situation? Damage is balanced in long group situations , but I agree that wizards dont do the most over time.<br>
<br>
It depends on who a wizard is grouped with. You get three tanks, an enchanter, a healer, and a wiz, its gonna be slower battles, less downtime.  If you have three wiz, an enchanter, and a healer, battles are faster but downtime is increased.<br>
<br>
A wizard IS efficient in experience groups. I was the first player on this server to hit 60 through grouping alone. Never soloed once. Doesnt that tell you something?<br>
<br>
 It depends on the group that you have. Groups can be caster heavy, tank heavy, and this effects what other classes you need to fill in the spots. The wizard needs an enchanter, maybe a tank to taunt. The tank needs a healer/buffer plus the enchanter. There are several variations to grouping and several places where certain combinations will work better than others.  Some mobs have a ton of hps and dont hit that hard. Thats good for a tank heavy group.  Some places have things that hit hard but have few hps. Many places have a mix of both.<br>
<br>
In order to get a good idea of what im talking about, group in Charasis one day. There is quite a diversity of mobs there, ranging from heavy hitters with few hit points to hp monsters that hit softly.  Velkator is kind of like this too Ive noticed. Dragon necropolis as well.<br>
<br>
